@coolasad : It totaly depends on torrent-program you use. In case of so called "partial downloads" your client (program) should report ONLY what you choose to download. That means that you'll appear as seeder for chosen (by you) files only.
I've said "should report" because none of the public trackers doesn't work reliably last couple of years.
DHT also reports successfully downloaded "chunks" of data and one's client derives that from DHT (if it works) and reports mentioned data too.
